WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.840
There are many islands in the sea near Scotland.

00:04.840 --> 00:08.760
This story is about one of these islands.

00:08.760 --> 00:12.920
The name of the island is Lana.

00:12.920 --> 00:17.040
Lana isn't big, but it's very beautiful.

00:17.040 --> 00:19.760
It's very quiet too.

00:19.760 --> 00:26.720
There are no houses or roads or cars on Lana, but there's a castle.

00:26.720 --> 00:30.880
The castle is very old.

00:30.880 --> 00:34.680
A young Scotsman lives in the castle.

00:34.680 --> 00:39.400
The Scotsman's name is Duncan McTavish.

00:39.400 --> 00:44.960
Duncan lives in the castle with his dog, Jock.

00:44.960 --> 00:49.120
Duncan is very happy on his island.

00:49.120 --> 00:52.160
He likes going for walks with Jock.

00:52.160 --> 00:57.480
He likes swimming and fishing in his little boat.

00:57.480 --> 01:01.040
There are many big rooms in Duncan's castle.

01:01.040 --> 01:09.440
They have a lot of old things in them, pictures and heavy tables, chairs and beds.

01:09.440 --> 01:14.240
In winter the castle is very cold and dark.

01:14.240 --> 01:21.200
Duncan puts on a lot of electric lights in all the rooms.

01:21.200 --> 01:25.840
One Monday morning in April, Duncan gets a letter.

01:25.840 --> 01:28.080
What's this?

01:28.080 --> 01:30.000
He asks.

01:30.000 --> 01:32.560
He opens the letter.

01:32.560 --> 01:35.920
It's from the electricity company.

01:35.920 --> 01:43.160
Duncan reads, electricity from October to March 5,000 pounds.

01:43.160 --> 01:50.320
Oh, Duncan says, I haven't got 5,000 pounds.

01:50.320 --> 01:52.320
What can I do?

01:52.320 --> 01:54.720
He's very unhappy.

01:54.720 --> 01:58.400
I can do only one thing.

01:58.400 --> 02:03.760
Sell my island and my castle.

02:03.760 --> 02:07.200
Duncan telephones a man in London.

02:07.200 --> 02:11.000
The man's name is Mr. Moneybags.

02:11.000 --> 02:16.520
Mr. Moneybags sells houses and castles.

02:16.520 --> 02:22.840
I want to sell my island and my castle, Duncan says.

02:22.840 --> 02:27.240
Okay, Mr. Moneybag says.

02:27.240 --> 02:31.760
Two days later he telephones Duncan.

02:31.760 --> 02:38.240
Leaping Larry wants to buy your island, he says.

02:38.240 --> 02:40.240
Leaping who?

02:40.240 --> 02:42.240
Duncan asks.

02:42.240 --> 02:43.240
Leaping Larry.

02:43.320 --> 02:47.960
You know, the famous American rock star.

02:47.960 --> 02:51.800
He wants to buy your island for his girlfriend.

02:51.800 --> 02:55.760
A rock star, Duncan says.

02:55.760 --> 02:58.040
Oh.

02:58.040 --> 03:04.200
He wants to see the island tomorrow afternoon, Mr. Moneybag says.

03:04.200 --> 03:06.200
Is that okay?

03:06.200 --> 03:09.680
Er, yes, Duncan says.

03:09.760 --> 03:13.600
Yes, of course.

03:13.600 --> 03:19.760
Leaping Larry and his girlfriend are coming to the island by helicopter.

03:19.760 --> 03:21.920
They're very late.

03:21.920 --> 03:26.160
Duncan and Jock wait a long time.

03:26.160 --> 03:29.760
Then the helicopter arrives.

03:29.760 --> 03:34.560
A tall man with long dark hair gets down from it.

03:34.560 --> 03:38.160
He's about 45 years old.

03:38.240 --> 03:40.240
There's a girl with him.

03:40.240 --> 03:45.520
She's about 20 and has long yellow hair.

03:45.520 --> 03:48.200
There's a small animal with her.

03:48.200 --> 03:52.880
The animal has long white hair.

03:52.880 --> 03:55.520
Hi, the man says.

03:55.520 --> 04:01.760
I'm Leaping Larry and this is my girlfriend Roxanne.

04:01.760 --> 04:04.640
Hi, Roxanne says.

04:04.640 --> 04:08.480
This is my dog, Bobo.

04:08.480 --> 04:11.360
Larry looks at the castle.

04:11.360 --> 04:15.600
Look at that old castle, Roxanne, he says.

04:15.600 --> 04:18.640
Don't you love it, honey?

04:18.640 --> 04:21.360
Roxanne doesn't smile.

04:21.360 --> 04:25.040
It's only an old castle.

04:25.040 --> 04:29.280
Leaping Larry and Roxanne go into the castle.

04:29.280 --> 04:31.360
It's very dark.

04:31.360 --> 04:33.920
Leaping Larry can't see.

04:34.000 --> 04:36.560
He falls down.

04:36.560 --> 04:38.480
Where are the lights?

04:38.480 --> 04:40.320
He asks.

04:40.320 --> 04:43.440
I'm sorry, Duncan says.

04:43.440 --> 04:45.840
There isn't any light.

04:45.840 --> 04:51.040
The company stopped my electricity this morning.

04:51.040 --> 04:55.600
I want some hot food, Roxanne says.

04:55.600 --> 04:58.320
I'm sorry, Duncan says.

04:58.320 --> 05:01.360
But I can't make hot food.

05:01.360 --> 05:04.400
I haven't got any electricity.

05:04.400 --> 05:07.280
But there is some cold food.

05:07.280 --> 05:10.480
Cold food, Roxanne says.

05:10.480 --> 05:12.480
Now thank you.

05:12.480 --> 05:14.480
I'm going to bed.

05:14.480 --> 05:17.920
But first I want a hot bath.

05:17.920 --> 05:21.680
And Bobo wants a bath too.

05:21.680 --> 05:25.040
I'm very sorry, Duncan says.

05:25.040 --> 05:28.000
But there's no hot water.

05:28.000 --> 05:32.000
No nights, no food, no hot water.

05:32.000 --> 05:33.840
Roxanne says.

05:33.840 --> 05:36.720
I don't like this place.

05:36.720 --> 05:40.000
Now, honey, Leaping Larry says.

05:40.000 --> 05:42.720
Don't call me honey.

05:42.720 --> 05:44.800
Roxanne says.

05:44.800 --> 05:47.920
Let's go, Bobo.

05:47.920 --> 05:51.680
Roxanne and Bobo go to bed.

05:51.680 --> 05:55.760
Larry and Duncan eat cold food and talk.

05:55.840 --> 05:58.240
Jock watches.

05:58.240 --> 06:01.520
Suddenly Roxanne screams.

06:01.520 --> 06:05.600
Duncan, Larry and Jock run to her room.

06:05.600 --> 06:09.200
Roxanne is in bed with Bobo.

06:09.200 --> 06:11.520
Honey, what's wrong?

06:11.520 --> 06:13.280
Larry asks.

06:13.280 --> 06:17.920
There was a noise in the room, Roxanne says.

06:17.920 --> 06:20.160
What was it?

06:20.160 --> 06:22.720
Duncan starts to smile.

06:22.720 --> 06:25.200
Why are you smiling?

06:25.200 --> 06:26.800
Roxanne says.

06:26.800 --> 06:29.280
She's very angry.

06:29.280 --> 06:33.280
Look at Jock, Duncan says.

06:33.280 --> 06:35.920
Jock is under the bed.

06:35.920 --> 06:39.040
He has a mouse in his mouth.

06:39.040 --> 06:42.480
A mouse, Roxanne says.

06:42.480 --> 06:43.920
She screams again.

06:47.040 --> 06:51.680
In the morning, Duncan and Leaping Larry are waiting.

06:51.680 --> 06:54.880
Roxanne and Bobo are late.

06:54.880 --> 06:58.960
They get up at 11 o'clock.

06:58.960 --> 07:02.480
Good morning, Duncan says.

07:02.480 --> 07:05.360
Roxanne doesn't answer.

07:05.360 --> 07:07.360
She says to Larry.

07:07.360 --> 07:10.560
Larry, I don't like this place.

07:10.560 --> 07:12.880
I want to go home.

07:12.880 --> 07:15.760
But honey, Larry says.

07:15.760 --> 07:18.240
Don't call me honey.

07:18.240 --> 07:20.400
Roxanne says.

07:20.480 --> 07:25.360
This castle is old, dark, and very cold.

07:25.360 --> 07:30.240
There's no electricity, no food, and no hot water.

07:30.240 --> 07:32.320
And I don't like it.

07:32.320 --> 07:35.040
Do you understand?

07:35.040 --> 07:37.840
Listen, honey, Larry says.

07:37.840 --> 07:41.200
We can build a big new house here.

07:41.200 --> 07:46.240
Our friends from California can come and stay.

07:46.240 --> 07:48.480
Duncan looks at Jock.

07:48.480 --> 07:51.600
Jock looks at Duncan.

07:51.600 --> 07:55.200
Build a big new house, they think.

07:55.200 --> 07:58.160
Oh, no.

07:58.160 --> 08:03.040
Leaping Larry says, we want to see the island.

08:03.040 --> 08:09.440
OK, Duncan says, we can go in my boat.

08:09.440 --> 08:14.080
Duncan, Larry, and Roxanne get into Duncan's boat.

08:14.080 --> 08:16.400
Jock gets in too.

08:16.400 --> 08:19.520
Bobo is with Roxanne.

08:19.520 --> 08:21.920
It's a beautiful day.

08:21.920 --> 08:25.920
But Roxanne isn't happy.

08:25.920 --> 08:28.640
What do you do all day?

08:28.640 --> 08:30.960
She asks Duncan.

08:30.960 --> 08:34.560
I go for walks, Duncan says.

08:34.560 --> 08:40.480
Sometimes I swim, and sometimes I catch fish.

08:40.480 --> 08:43.680
Oh, Roxanne says.

08:43.680 --> 08:46.720
That isn't very interesting.

08:46.720 --> 08:49.440
Listen, honey, Larry says.

08:49.440 --> 08:52.560
We can make the island interesting.

08:52.560 --> 08:55.280
I know people with film companies.

08:55.280 --> 08:58.080
They can come here and make films.

08:58.080 --> 09:00.960
Hundreds of films.

09:00.960 --> 09:03.280
Duncan looks at Jock.

09:03.280 --> 09:06.400
Jock looks at Duncan.

09:06.400 --> 09:09.360
Film companies, they think.

09:09.360 --> 09:12.240
Oh, no.

09:12.240 --> 09:15.760
Duncan is very unhappy.

09:15.760 --> 09:20.560
He doesn't want to sell his island and his castle to Larry.

09:20.560 --> 09:24.320
He doesn't want film companies or Larry's friends

09:24.320 --> 09:26.320
on the island.

09:26.320 --> 09:28.960
But what can Duncan do?

09:28.960 --> 09:33.440
The electricity company wants 5,000 pounds.

09:33.440 --> 09:35.600
He has no money.

09:35.600 --> 09:39.680
He can't stay in his castle.

09:39.680 --> 09:44.640
Duncan, Larry, and Roxanne are all sitting in Duncan's boat.

09:44.640 --> 09:47.680
Jock and Bobo are wisdom.

09:47.680 --> 09:51.920
Suddenly, Jock sees a rabbit on the island.

09:51.920 --> 09:54.640
Jock loves catching rabbits.

09:54.640 --> 09:59.840
He jumps into the sea and starts to swim to the island.

09:59.840 --> 10:03.680
Bobo thinks, this is interesting.

10:03.680 --> 10:06.960
And he jumps in too.

10:06.960 --> 10:08.880
Bobo is in the water.

10:08.880 --> 10:10.800
Roxanne screams.

10:10.800 --> 10:12.880
Jump into the sea, Larry.

10:12.880 --> 10:14.720
Get Bobo.

10:14.720 --> 10:17.760
But Larry doesn't move.

10:17.760 --> 10:20.000
Why are you raining?

10:20.000 --> 10:23.680
Roxanne says, jump in.

10:23.680 --> 10:28.640
But honey, Larry says, I can't swim.

10:28.640 --> 10:30.160
Can't swim?

10:30.160 --> 10:35.120
Roxanne says, she is very angry.

10:35.120 --> 10:37.600
Look, Duncan says,

10:37.600 --> 10:39.680
Bobo is OK.

10:39.680 --> 10:42.720
He's having a good time.

10:42.720 --> 10:46.240
Bobo is swimming in the water with Jock.

10:46.240 --> 10:50.640
But Roxanne is very angry with Larry.

10:50.640 --> 10:54.000
You don't love me, she says.

10:54.000 --> 10:57.680
And you don't love me, Larry says.

10:57.680 --> 11:00.640
You only love Bobo.

11:00.640 --> 11:04.080
You're right, Roxanne says.

11:04.080 --> 11:08.400
She stands in the boat and starts to hit Larry.

11:08.400 --> 11:11.840
Don't do that, Duncan says.

11:11.840 --> 11:13.600
The boat moves.

11:13.600 --> 11:17.200
Roxanne falls into the water.

11:17.200 --> 11:20.160
She starts to scream.

11:20.160 --> 11:23.680
Roxanne is making a lot of noise.

11:23.680 --> 11:27.920
Jock sees Roxanne in the water with Bobo.

11:27.920 --> 11:29.600
What are they doing?

11:29.600 --> 11:32.400
Are they playing a new game?

11:32.400 --> 11:34.960
Jock wants to play too.

11:34.960 --> 11:37.520
He swings to Bobo.

11:37.520 --> 11:41.920
Don't worry, Roxanne screams.

11:41.920 --> 11:45.440
Duncan brings the boat near Roxanne.

11:45.440 --> 11:48.400
Roxanne gets into the boat.

11:48.400 --> 11:52.320
Then Bobo gets into the boat.

11:52.320 --> 11:56.560
Roxanne is very angry.

11:56.560 --> 11:59.760
Take me back to California.

11:59.760 --> 12:05.440
Now, she says to Larry.

12:05.440 --> 12:11.840
Later, Larry, Roxanne and Bobo get into their helicopter.

12:11.840 --> 12:15.200
Goodbye, Duncan says.

12:15.200 --> 12:18.960
Larry and Roxanne don't answer.

12:18.960 --> 12:22.080
The helicopter goes away.

12:22.080 --> 12:24.560
Duncan smiles at Jock.

12:24.560 --> 12:27.600
He's very happy.

12:27.680 --> 12:33.280
Leaping Larry isn't going to buy our island, he says.

12:33.280 --> 12:36.160
That's good.

12:36.160 --> 12:40.480
But Duncan has big money problems.

12:40.480 --> 12:44.480
Leaping Larry doesn't want to buy the island.

12:44.480 --> 12:51.200
But where can Duncan get 5,000 pounds for the electricity company?

12:51.200 --> 12:57.120
Later, Duncan telephones Mr Moneybacks in London.

12:57.120 --> 13:02.400
Leaping Larry telephoned me, Mr Moneybacks says.

13:02.400 --> 13:04.880
He doesn't like your island.

13:04.880 --> 13:07.680
He doesn't want to buy it.

13:07.680 --> 13:11.280
And I'm not going to sell it for you now.

13:11.280 --> 13:13.760
It's your problem.

13:13.760 --> 13:14.320
Goodbye.

13:17.360 --> 13:21.360
Duncan goes for a long walk with Jock.

13:21.360 --> 13:23.840
He's very unhappy.

13:23.840 --> 13:27.280
They walk to a place across the island.

13:27.280 --> 13:31.040
And there Duncan sees a girl.

13:31.040 --> 13:35.840
She's looking at the sea and she's painting a picture.

13:35.840 --> 13:39.840
Near her is a small boat.

13:39.840 --> 13:44.240
Good afternoon, Duncan says.

13:44.240 --> 13:46.800
The girl looks at Duncan.

13:46.800 --> 13:48.640
She's beautiful.

13:48.640 --> 13:51.200
He likes her.

13:51.280 --> 13:52.560
Who are you?

13:52.560 --> 13:54.080
She asks.

13:54.080 --> 13:57.680
What do you want?

13:57.680 --> 14:01.520
I'm Duncan McTavish, Duncan says.

14:01.520 --> 14:03.120
I live here.

14:03.120 --> 14:05.680
Lana is my island.

14:05.680 --> 14:09.360
And this is my dog, Jock.

14:09.360 --> 14:11.600
Jock looks at the girl.

14:11.600 --> 14:14.320
He likes her too.

14:14.320 --> 14:18.080
Lana is your island, the girl says.

14:18.160 --> 14:21.520
Oh, I'm Jean Stewart.

14:21.520 --> 14:23.200
I'm a teacher.

14:23.200 --> 14:26.640
I work in a school across the sea.

14:26.640 --> 14:31.040
Today is a holiday and the school is closed.

14:31.040 --> 14:34.080
I came here in my boat.

14:34.080 --> 14:37.040
I wanted to paint your island.

14:37.040 --> 14:42.560
The light is very good and the colors are very beautiful.

14:42.560 --> 14:46.160
I can paint good pictures here.

14:46.240 --> 14:49.520
Duncan looks at Jean's picture.

14:49.520 --> 14:51.440
Yes, he says.

14:51.440 --> 14:54.560
Your picture is very good.

14:54.560 --> 14:57.840
Thank you, Jean says.

14:57.840 --> 15:01.920
Duncan and Jean talk for a long time.

15:01.920 --> 15:05.280
Where do you live, Jean asks?

15:05.280 --> 15:09.120
I live in a castle, Duncan says.

15:09.120 --> 15:11.600
Come and see it.

15:11.600 --> 15:15.840
Duncan, Jean and Jock go to the castle.

15:15.840 --> 15:20.320
Your castle is beautiful, Jean says.

15:20.320 --> 15:22.400
Yes, Duncan says.

15:22.400 --> 15:25.680
But it's very cold and dark.

15:25.680 --> 15:28.160
There's no electricity.

15:28.160 --> 15:30.480
I have no money.

15:30.480 --> 15:33.440
I love my island very much.

15:33.440 --> 15:36.960
But I can't make money from it.

15:36.960 --> 15:39.680
Jean looks at the castle.

15:39.680 --> 15:44.720
Suddenly, she says, yes, you can.

15:44.720 --> 15:45.600
How?

15:45.600 --> 15:47.600
Duncan asks.

15:47.600 --> 15:52.400
People can come here for holidays, Jean says.

15:52.400 --> 15:55.840
They can paint pictures of your island.

15:55.840 --> 16:01.200
I can teach them and they can stay in your castle.

16:01.200 --> 16:04.720
We can make a lot of money.

16:04.720 --> 16:07.520
Duncan looks at Jock.

16:07.520 --> 16:10.720
Jock looks at Duncan.

16:10.720 --> 16:15.280
You're right, Duncan says.

16:15.280 --> 16:21.120
Now, look tabish painting the holidays are very famous.

16:21.120 --> 16:25.040
Every year, many visitors come to the island.

16:25.040 --> 16:27.360
They stay in the castle.

16:27.360 --> 16:31.520
They go for walks and paint beautiful pictures.

16:31.520 --> 16:35.600
They take their pictures back to their homes.

16:35.600 --> 16:40.560
The rooms in the castle aren't cold and dark now.

16:40.560 --> 16:44.160
Duncan and Jean have a lot of money.

16:44.160 --> 16:48.400
There is no problem with the electricity company.

16:48.400 --> 16:52.240
And Jean makes very good food.

16:52.240 --> 16:56.720
The visitors are very happy.

16:56.720 --> 17:00.480
Duncan and Jean are married now.

17:00.480 --> 17:05.280
They have two children, a boy and a girl.

17:05.280 --> 17:09.680
Jock loves playing with the children.

17:09.760 --> 17:13.760
Duncan often sits in his little boat.

17:13.760 --> 17:20.480
Sometimes he catches a fish, but usually he sleeps.

17:20.480 --> 17:25.600
He's a happy man.

